remarks: "Calemos", one of the syllogisms of Aristotelian logic.  All ` ph ` is ` ps ` (PaM), no ` ps ` is ` ch ` (MeS), and ` ch ` exist, therefore some ` ch ` is not ` ph ` (SoP).  (In Aristotelian notation, AEO-4:  PaM and MeS therefore SoP.) (Contributed by David A. Wheeler, 28-Aug-2016.) (Revised by David A. Wheeler, 2-Sep-2016.)
statement:
calemos.maj $e |- A. x ( ph -> ps ) $.
calemos.min $e |- A. x ( ps -> -. ch ) $.
calemos.e $e |- E. x ch $.
calemos $p |- E. x ( ch /\ -. ph ) $.
